  "prompt": "How long should a full time SDE at an Amazon interview preparation take, assuming a moderate level of preparation at this point?",
  "response": "For a full-time Software Development Engineer (SDE) role at Amazon, a typical comprehensive interview preparation timeline might look like this:\n\n1. Data Structures & Algorithms Preparation:\n- 2-3 months of consistent practice\n- 2-4 hours daily\n- Focus on LeetCode/HackerRank problems\n- Cover all major data structures and algorithm patterns\n\n2. System Design:\n- 3-4 weeks\n- 1-2 hours daily\n- Study fundamentals and practice mock system design interviews\n- Read system design books/resources\n\n3. Behavioral Interview Preparation:\n- 2-3 weeks\n- Prepare Amazon's Leadership Principles stories\n- Practice STAR method responses\n- 1 hour daily rehearsing scenarios\n\n4. Mock Interviews:\n- 2-4 weeks\n- 2-3 mock technical interviews\n- 2-3 mock behavioral interviews\n- Analyze and improve weak areas\n\nTotal Estimated Preparation Time:\n- 3-5 months\n- Approximately 15-25 hours per week\n- Consistency and quality of preparation matters more than pure time spent\n\nFactors affecting timeline:\n- Current skill level\n- Prior coding interview experience\n- Daily time commitment\n- Learning efficiency\n\nRecommendation: Start early, be systematic, and continuously track progress.",
